description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Generic Therapy Assistant&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be working across the inpatient therapy teams and will support the physiotherapists/occupational therapists in providing rehabilitation interventions to patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will involve a wide range of duties including assisting the physiotherapist/occupational therapists to deliver treatment programmes to patients, clerical, administration, involving work with computers and housekeeping duties. The posts will support the timely discharge of patients from the orthopaedic wards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be expected to have a good standard of general education including maths, English and basic computer skills. Recent and relevant experience in a health care setting is essential. The successful candidate will have excellent communication skills and will show a good awareness of patients needs. We are looking for someone who is flexible and enthusiastic. This is a physically demanding role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is essential to be able to show initiative, to be able to work effectively without direct supervision and to be able to take responsibility for delegated duties, under the guidance of a physiotherapist/occupational therapist.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameGraeme LambertJob titleAHP Inpatient ManagerEmail addressgraeme.lambert@nhs.netTelephone number0151 678 5111 ext 2624&lt;/p&gt;
